spec: as3361
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(asyncio)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 671 (as3361): __invert__, __floor__, __ceil__ dict-presence (unary ~x, math.floor(x), math.ceil(x)) for asyncio types."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
    - "Classes covered: asyncio.Task, asyncio.Future, asyncio.Event, asyncio.Lock, asyncio.Semaphore, asyncio.BoundedSemaphore, asyncio.Condition, asyncio.Queue, asyncio.PriorityQueue, asyncio.LifoQueue."
    - "Key finding (__invert__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __invert__. Bitwise inversion (__invert__, ~x) belongs to the integer numeric data model (numbers.Integral). asyncio types are coroutine-based concurrency primitives — none of them model an integer bitfield. ~event, ~task, ~queue are not valid Python expressions for asyncio objects. asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition are boolean-state synchronization guards; bitwise inversion of a synchronization object is not defined. asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore encapsulate a permit counter fully behind acquire()/release() coroutines; ~semaphore is not a valid Python expression. asyncio.Task/Future are pending coroutine result handles with no integer data model; ~task is not defined. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue are ordered item stores; ~queue is not defined."
    - "Key finding (__floor__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __floor__. The math.floor() built-in delegates to __floor__ when defined on the argument type; otherwise it attempts __index__ or __int__ conversion (both also absent from asyncio types, as established in wave 653). __floor__ is part of the numbers.Real protocol. asyncio types implement no numeric data model of any kind — confirmed false across waves 658–670 for all arithmetic, bitwise, reflected arithmetic, reflected bitwise, in-place augmented assignment, and unary numeric operators. math.floor(event), math.floor(task), math.floor(queue) are not meaningful operations for synchronization primitives, coroutine handles, or item stores."
    - "Key finding (__ceil__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __ceil__. The math.ceil() built-in delegates to __ceil__ when defined, analogously to __floor__. __ceil__ is part of the numbers.Real protocol. asyncio types have no numeric magnitude that could be rounded up. math.ceil(event), math.ceil(task), math.ceil(queue) are not defined operations for any asyncio type. The rationale is identical to __floor__: asyncio objects interact entirely through await, async with, async for, and explicit method calls — never through Python's numeric rounding protocol."
    - "Continues the all-false run from wave 656 (__call__/__len__/__getitem__) through wave 671 (__invert__/__floor__/__ceil__) — sixteen consecutive waves of 100% false results for asyncio types."
    - "Cross-wave summary for asyncio subjects:"
    - "  Wave 656 (as3136): __call__/__len__/__getitem__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 657 (as3151): __setitem__/__delitem__/__contains__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 658 (as3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 659 (as3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 660 (as3196): __pow__/__lshift__/__rshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 661 (as3211): __and__/__or__/__xor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 662 (as3226): __radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 663 (as3241): __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 664 (as3256): __rpow__/__rlshift__/__rrshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 665 (as3271): __rand__/__ror__/__rxor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 666 (as3286): __iadd__/__isub__/__imul__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 667 (as3301): __itruediv__/__ifloordiv__/__imod__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 668 (as3316): __ipow__/__ilshift__/__irshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 669 (as3331): __iand__/__ior__/__ixor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 670 (as3346): __neg__/__pos__/__abs__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 671 (as3361): __invert__/__floor__/__ceil__ — all false for all 10."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __invert__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__invert__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __invert__.
# Bitwise inversion (__invert__, ~x) belongs to the integer numeric data model
#   (numbers.Integral). asyncio types are coroutine-based concurrency primitives
#   with no integer representation.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition: boolean-state synchronization guards;
#   ~event, ~lock, ~condition are not valid Python expressions.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: permit-counter objects whose internal
#   integer state is fully encapsulated behind acquire()/release() coroutines.
#   The counter is not exposed for bitwise inversion.
# asyncio.Task/Future: pending coroutine result handles; ~task, ~future are
#   not valid Python expressions.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: ordered item stores with no integer
#   data model; ~queue is not a defined Python expression.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table as3361.invert:
