# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __ceil__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__ceil__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __ceil__.
# math.ceil() delegates to __ceil__ (numbers.Real protocol), analogously to
#   __floor__. asyncio types have no numeric magnitude that could be rounded up.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition: boolean-state guards; rounding a synchronization
#   object is not a meaningful operation.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: permit-counter objects; the internal
#   counter is fully encapsulated and not exposed through rounding protocol.
# asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles; math.ceil(task) and
#   math.ceil(future) are not valid Python expressions.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: ordered item stores; math.ceil(queue)
#   is not defined. Queue length is accessed via qsize(), not ceil().
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

